    {
      "name": " GameText_04_EnglishTutorialSection",
      "entries": [
        {
          "key": 18,
          "value": " Attack"
        },
        {
          "key": 27,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Attack</color></b></style> \n\nUse  {ButtonWest}  to attack and create combos with your sword.\n\nPress {RightShoulder} at the end of combos to inflict extra damage on the enemy."
        },
        {
          "key": 19,
          "value": " Lock On"
        },
        {
          "key": 28,
          "value": " <style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Lock On</color></b></style> \n\nPress  <size=135%>{RightStick}</size>  to lock on/off the enemy."
        },
        {
          "key": 20,
          "value": " Perfect Dodge"
        },
        {
          "key": 29,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Perfect Dodge</color></b></style> \r\n\r\nDodging <i>right before</i> an enemy attack triggers <color=#00FFFF><b>Slows Down</b></color> .\r\n\r\nUse  {ButtonSouth}  <i>right before</i> enemy attacks.\r"
        },
        {
          "key": 21,
          "value": " Elemental Fist"
        },
        {
          "key": 30,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Elemental Fist</color></b></style> \r\n\r\nSome enemies have <color=red>Barriers</color> that can only be broken via <color=#cbadff>Elemental Fist</color>.\r\n\r\nYou can use <color=#cbadff>Elemental Fist</color> by pressing {LeftTrigger} after charging <color=yellow>Elemental Gauge</color>.\n\r\nYou can charge <color=yellow>Elemental Gauge</color> through <color=#00FFFF>attacks</color> and <color=#00FFFF>Perfect Dodge</color>."
        },
        {
          "key": 22,
          "value": " Weakness"
        },
        {
          "key": 31,
          "value": " <style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Weakness</color></b></style> \n\nThe only way to break an enemy's barrier is to use the correct <color=#cbadff>Elemental</color> type (see to the left). \n\nSome monsters have <color=red>Stronger Barriers</color> that require multiple strikes from the Elemental Fist. \n\nThe <color=green>stronger</color> your bond with your confidants is, the more times your elemental fist will strike the barrier."
        },
        {
          "key": 23,
          "value": " Fast Travel"
        },
        {
          "key": 32,
          "value": " <style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Fast Travel</color></b></style> \n\nUse {Interact} to access the fast-travel menu.\nYou are only able to fast-travel to areas you've visited before.\n\n<style=h3><b><color=#00FF66>*Tip 1*</color></b></style>\nSome, but not all, fast-travel areas allow you to <color=#00FFFF>SAVE</color> through the main menu by pressing  <size=135%>{MenuStart}</size>.\n\n<style=h3><b><color=#00FF66>*Tip 2*</color></b></style>\nAll tutorials are stored in the main menu."
        },
        {
          "key": 24,
          "value": " Dateable Skill"
        },
        {
          "key": 33,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Dateable Skills</color></b></style> \r\n\r\nPressing {RightTrigger}  will show you dateable skills you can use.\r\n\r\nUse {Dpad}  to cycle through them and {MenuConfirm} to confirm.\r\n\r\nUsing the dateable skill consumes <color=#ff8830>SP</color>.\r\n<color=#ff8830>SP</color> can't be restored manually.\r"
        },
        {
          "key": 25,
          "value": "Skill Tree & Essences"
        },
        {
          "key": 34,
          "value": " <style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Skill Tree & Essences</color></b></style> \r\n\r\nSome enemies give you <color=#cbadff>Black Essence</color>.\r\n\r\nYou can use these points to upgrade your skills in the <color=#cbadff>Skill Tree</color>.\r\n\r\nUse <sprite name=\"PS_START\"> to access the <color=#cbadff>Skill Tree</color> through the main menu.\r\n\n<style=h3><b><color=#00FF66>*Tip*</color></b></style> \r\nYou can also pick up essence while exploring the dungeon.\r"
        },
        {
          "key": 26,
          "value": " Calendar"
        },
        {
          "key": 35,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Calendar Gameplay</color></b></style> \r\n\r\nYou are free to spend your day as you’d like. \r\n\r\nHowever, you don’t have unlimited time. The <color=red><b>Wall</b></color> must be dealt with before the <color=red><b>Timer</b></color> runs out.\r\n\r\nYou can talk to <color=#00FFFF>Aria</color> at the <b>Hologram Station</b> to go to the <color=red><b>Wall</b></color>.\r"
        },
        {
          "key": 114,
          "value": " Stinger"
        },
        {
          "key": 121,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Stinger </color></b></style> \r\n\r\nPress {ButtonNorth} while holding {RightShoulder} to use the <b>Stinger</b>.\r\n\r\n<color=#cbadff>A powerful sword thrust</color> that moves you closer to enemies while also damaging them.\r\n\r\n<style=h3><b><color=#00FF66>*Tip*</color></b></style>\r\nThis skill <color=#00FFFF>knocks down</color> enemies.\r"
        },
        {
          "key": 115,
          "value": " Blast"
        },
        {
          "key": 122,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Blast</color></b></style> \r\n\r\nPress {ButtonEast} while holding {RightShoulder} to shoot a <color=#cbadff>damaging wave of energy</color> towards your target.\r"
        },
        {
          "key": 116,
          "value": " AOE"
        },
        {
          "key": 123,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>AOE </color></b></style> \r\n\r\nPress {ButtonWest} while holding {RightShoulder} to use <b>AOE attack</b>.\r\n\r\n<b>AOE attack</b> <color=#cbadff> creates an area of damage </color> around you.\r"
        },
        {
          "key": 117,
          "value": " Three Sword"
        },
        {
          "key": 124,
          "value": " <style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Three Sword </color></b></style> \n\nPress {ButtonSouth} while holding {RightShoulder} to summon <b>Three Swords</b> to attack enemies in your immediate area.\n\n<style=h3><b><color=#00FF66>*Tip*</color></b></style> \nDeveloping a stronger bond with Sia will make this skill stronger."
        },
        {
          "key": 118,
          "value": " Great Sword"
        },
        {
          "key": 125,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Great Sword</color></b></style> \r\n\rUse  {ButtonNorth}  to use <b>Great Sword</b>.\r\n\r\n<style=h3><b><color=#00FF66>*Tip*</color></b></style>\r\nYour great sword is capable of penetrating through enemy shields.\r\n"
        },
        {
          "key": 119,
          "value": " DeathBlow"
        },
        {
          "key": 126,
          "value": " <style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Deathblow</color></b></style> \n\nAllows you to give devastating damage to the target enemy. Press {ButtonEast} when you see the indicator. This will be activated when you've struck the enemy continuously for a particular duration.\n\n<style=h3><b><color=#00FF66>*Tip*</color></b></style>\nThis skill will destroy smaller types of enemies <color=#00FFFF><b>instantly</b></color>."
        },
        {
          "key": 120,
          "value": " All Out Attack"
        },
        {
          "key": 127,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>All Out Attack</color></b></style> \r\n\r\nYou can use the “All out attack” by filling up the four circles that make up the The “All out attack” gauge. You fill these circles by using elemental attacks. \r\n\r\nOnce fully charged, press the left {LeftShoulder} and the right {RightShoulder} together to initiate the <color=#00FFFF>All Out Attack</color>.\r\n\r\n<style=h3><b><color=#00FF66>*Tip*</color></b></style> \r\n“All out attack” allows you to destroy <b><color=red>any type of barrier</color></b>\r"
        },
        {
          "key": 128,
          "value": " Sprint"
        },
        {
          "key": 129,
          "value": " <style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Sprint</color></b></style> \n\nPress the left stick {LeftStick} <color=#00FFFF><b>once</b></color> while running to sprint."
        },
        {
          "key": 147,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Calendar Gameplay 2</color></b></style> \r\n\r\n<style=h3><b><color=#00FF66>*Note 1*</color></b></style> \r\nYou are <color=#FF0000>unable</color> to go to the wall <color=#FF0000>at night</color>. So, remember to plan accordingly. \r\n\r\n<style=h3><b><color=#00FF66>*Note 2*</color></b></style> \r\nSpend time with your confidants in order to become more powerful.\r"
        },
        {
          "key": 148,
          "value": " Calendar Tip"
        },
        {
          "key": 164,
          "value": " <style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Walk Quietly</color></b></style> \n\n<color=#00FFFF><b>Gently</b></color> push the left stick {LeftStick} forward to walk quietly."
        },
        {
          "key": 165,
          "value": " <style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Sia Bike</color></b></style> \n\nUse the left stick {LeftStick} to control the bike and avoid obstacles. Use the {ButtonWest} to shoot missiles that can destroy energy walls."
        },
        {
          "key": 166,
          "value": " <style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Sia’s Lab</color></b></style> \n\nWhen you want to talk to Sia, you can visit her in her lab towards the front of the train."
        },
        {
          "key": 167,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Plan Computer</color></b></style> \r\n\r\nNow that Aria is gone, you have to plan out your own day. Use this computer when you want to <color=#00FFFF>Go to Wall</color>.\r\n\r\nRemember, you are <color=#FF0000>unable to go to the wall at night</color>. So, remember to plan accordingly. \r"
        },
        {
          "key": 168,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Instant Heal</color></b></style> \r\n\r\nYuna can now heal you instantly. \r\n\r\n<style=h3><b><color=#00FF66>*Unlock*</color></b></style> \r\nYou can unlock Yuna’s skills in her skill tree page.\r"
        },
        {
          "key": 169,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Ice Rain</color></b></style> \r\n\r\nSia will rain down sharp, damaging, ice atop your enemies.\r\n\r\n<style=h3><b><color=#00FF66>*Unlock*</color></b></style> \r\nYou can unlock Sia’s skills in her skill tree page.\r"
        },
        {
          "key": 170,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Min Barrier</color></b></style> \r\n\r\nMin can summon a shield that protects you from a single enemy attack regardless of strength.\r\n\r\n<style=h3><b><color=#00FF66>*Unlock*</color></b></style> \r\nYou can unlock Min’s skills in her skill tree page.\r"
        },
        {
          "key": 172,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Yohan’s Car</color></b></style>\r\n\r\nWhen you want to talk to Yohan, you can visit him in his <color=#00FFFF>car</color>, which is right next to Sia’s.\r"
        },
        {
          "key": 173,
          "value": " <style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Save</color></b></style> \n\nYou can save your progress near fast travel points.\n\n<style=h3><b><color=#00FF66>*Tip*</color></b></style> \nEternights <color=#00FFFF>autosaves</color> frequently. You can find this save at the top of the load list."
        },
        {
          "key": 174,
          "value": " <style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Precious Memories</color></b></style> \n\nThese are the last days you will get to spend with these characters. Make sure to spend them <i>wisely</i>.\n\n<style=h3><b><color=#00FF66>*Tip*</color></b></style> \nTry and see if you can <color=#00FFFF>max</color> out your relationship with at least one character."
        },
        {
          "key": 816,
          "value": "<style=h3><b><color=#00FF66>Elemental Fist is Ready!</color></b></style>\n\nPress {LeftTrigger}  to  break <b><color=red>Barriers</color>."
        },
        {
          "key": 817,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>QTE</color></b></style> \r\n\r\nPress {ButtonWest} when the outer circle reaches within the <b><color=#00FFFF>colored range</color></b>.\r"
        },
        {
          "key": 820,
          "value": "<style=Title><b><color=#9a75ff>Parry</color></b></style> \r\n\r\nPress {ButtonEast} <i>right before</i> an enemy attack triggered by <color=#0000FF><b>blue</b></color> color will parry the enemy attack.\r\n\r\nSuccessful parry gives you a boost to the <b>Death Blow</b>."
        }
      ]
    },
